main event: A small object was observed on radar categorized as a probable satellite on 9 November 1962.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 1 minute., The object appeared as a bright star in flight to the East., The sighting was conducted using ground radar., The observation was categorized with a very high level of visibility., No photographs were available for this sighting.
witness description: crew members of an aircraft involved in the sighting
